<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#15)]" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d710a-15">
                            <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi></head>
                            <p>—While <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> was having
                                luncheon with <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d710a-15fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_79">p. 79</ref>.</note>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> was a luncheon guest
                                at <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>’s quarters in
                                    Babelsberg.<note n="2" xml:id="d710a-15fn2">London <hi rend="italic">Times</hi>, July 19, 1945, p. 4.</note> No
                                record of the substance of the conversation at this meeting has been
                                found.</p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>